description: Returns all the available versions for the specified Amazon Connect instance and view identifier. Results will be sorted from highest to lowest.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instanceId in the ARN of the instance.

parameters.name: ViewId
parameters.description: The identifier of the view. Both ViewArn and ViewId can be used.

nested_items.name: ViewVersionSummaryList
nested_items.description: A list of view version summaries.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the view version.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the view version.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description of the view version.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the view version.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of the view version.

nested_items.name: Version
nested_items.description: The sequentially incremented version of the view version.

nested_items.name: VersionDescription
nested_items.description: The description of the view version.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of results. Use the value returned in the previous response in the next request to retrieve the next set of results.
